creator.title: Rapper and Songwriter
creator.biography: French Montana, born Karim Kharbouch, is a Moroccan-American rapper and songwriter. He gained popularity with his mixtapes and collaborations with artists such as Rick Ross, Diddy, and Drake. He has released several studio albums, including "Excuse My French" and "Jungle Rules," which earned him mainstream success with hit singles like "Unforgettable" and "No Stylist." Montana is known for his fusion of rap and pop, and for his unique flow and rhyming style. He has also been involved in humanitarian work and supports education for underprivileged children.
